Package com.rapidminer.belt.column

Class Statistics.Result

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rapidminer.belt.column.Statistics.Result
  • Enclosing class:
    Statistics
    public static final class Statistics.Result
extends java.lang.Object
    Result container for a statistics computation. Not all values might be set depending on column type and statistic.

    Statistics for columns of type ColumnTypes.REAL and ColumnTypes.INTEGER only make use of the numeric value (see getNumeric()).

    Statistics for columns of type ColumnTypes.NOMINAL make use of the categorical index and string value (see getCategorical() and getObject() respectively). An exception is the statistic Statistics.Statistic.COUNT which makes use of the numeric value (see getNumeric()) instead.

    Statistics for columns of type ColumnTypes.DATETIME and ColumnTypes.TIME only make use of the Instant and LocalTime value respectively (see getObject()). An exception is the statistic Statistics.Statistic.COUNT which makes use of the numeric value (see getNumeric()) instead.

    Statistics for custom column types of category Column.Category.CATEGORICAL and Column.Category.OBJECT show the same behavior as nominal and date-time columns respectively.
